      <div class="msgContentFrame">&lt;Hmmm...&gt; &lt;That's interesting&gt;  Thanks for response.   <br /> <br />Paying attention to combat logs, looks like Profundity does put up bigger numbers per nuke (which in turn is a bigger SP return per proc), however: Profundity also has the effect of slowing down recast timers.  Interesting trade off. <br /> <br />Dark seal seems pretty meh.  With November patch increasing native spell accuracy too, we'll have to see if it becomes completely irrelevant for the foreseeable future. <br /> <br />I never realized that's how Initiation works.  IIRC, Initiation can transfer up to four beneficial (4) spell affects.  With the relatively short timer on Absorb spells, it would be hard to stick four (4) spells on a mob and transfer the affects to a tank before the affects start wearing off.  In theory though, this could make some really interesting encounters.</div>
